SIMPLE: taster
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taster
<hw>Tast"er</hw> <pr>(t⟦amac⟧st"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who tastes; especially, one who first tastes food or drink to
ascertain its quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy tutor be thy <qex>taster</qex>, ere thou eat.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That in which, or by which, anything is tasted, as,
a dram cup, a cheese taster, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a peculiar kind of zooids
situated on the polyp-stem of certain Siphonophora. They somewhat
resemble the feeding zooids, but are destitute of mouths. See
<er>Siphonophora</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tastily</ent>⟦br⟧
